                        <div class="bg-blue-500 text-white rounded-t-lg p-4">
                            <h3 class="text-lg font-bold text-center">By-Laws of the Faculty and Personnel Association</h3>
                        </div>
                        <div class="p-4">
                            <div class="space-y-4">
                                <h1 class="text-2xl font-bold text-center">Constitution and By-Laws of the Faculty and Personnel Association of the </br> Laguna State Polytechnic University</h1>
                               
                                </br>

                                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-center">PREAMBLE</h2>
                                <p>WE the members of the Faculty and Personnel Association of the Laguna State Polytechnic University in order to establish an association based on truth, justice, equality, and peace under a democratic rule of law do promulgate this constitution with the Almighty's blessings.</p>
                            
                                </br>

                                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-center">ARTICLE I - NAME</h2>
                                <p>This association shall be known as the "Faculty and Personnel Association of the Laguna State Polytechnic University Santa Cruz Laguna."</p>
                                
                                </br>

                                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-center">ARTICLE II - PRINCIPLES</h2>
                                <ol class="list-decimal ml-4">
                                    <li>Bind the members so that there shall be unity.</li>
                                    <li>Establish an organization so as to have a harmonious relation with the school administration based on mutual respect.</li>
                                    <li>Form a set of officers whose prime duty is to serve and protect the members.</li>
                                    <li>Adhere to the Constitution of the Republic of the Philippines and to the rules and regulations of the CHED.</li>
                                </ol>
                                
                                </br>
                                
                                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-center">ARTICLE III - MEMBERSHIP</h2>
                                <ol class="list-decimal ml-4">
                                    <li>All faculty and personnel who are holders of permanent and provisional appointments shall be members of this association.</li>
                                    <li>All casual employees, job orders, and part-time teachers who have two (2) consecutive years of service shall be provisional members of this association. Membership expires upon termination of service from the University.</li>
                                </ol>
                                
                                </br>

                                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-center">ARTICLE IV - OFFICERS</h2>
                                <ol class="list-decimal ml-4">
                                    <li>The officers shall be composed of a president, a vice-president, a secretary, a treasurer, an auditor, two business managers, and two press relation officers.</li>
                                    <li>The officers shall be selected through an election called for this purpose and shall be voted upon by the plurality of all members.</li>
                                    <li>All the officers will serve for two years with re-election.</li>
                                    <li>Elections will be held on the second Monday after the opening of the regular classes of the first semester.</li>
                                    <li>Oath-taking of officers will be held one month after the election.</li>
                                </ol>
                                
                                </br>
                                
                                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-center">ARTICLE V - DUTIES OF THE OFFICERS</h2>
                                <ol class="list-decimal ml-4">
                                    <li><strong>The President.</strong> The president shall act as the executive of the association. His duties are the following:
                                        <ol class="list-decimal ml-4">
                                            <li>Preside over all the meetings of the association.</li>
                                            <li>Select or appoint anybody from the association to represent him in any forum, appoint or create a board if necessary.</li>
                                            <li>Pronounce any project of the association, likewise report any project/projects accomplished.</li>
                                            <li>Sign and approve documents, orders, letters of the association.</li>
                                            <li>Call meetings as need arises.</li>
                                        </ol>
                                    </li>
                                    <li><strong>The Vice-President.</strong> The vice president shall act or preside as the president does whenever the president is absent; preside over a meeting when the president is participating in a debate or discussion.</li>
                                    <li><strong>The Secretary.</strong> The secretary shall keep all documents of the association, shall prepare the minutes of every meeting, shall prepare the calling of meetings, shall act on any undertakings that the officers/association has approved.</li>
                                    <li><strong>The Treasurer.</strong> The treasurer shall keep the money of the association, shall keep the data on collection and disbursements, shall render a statement of accounts.</li>
                                    <li><strong>The Auditor.</strong> The auditor shall audit the financial statement if the association has programs, parties, or undertakings with other associations.</li>
                                    <li><strong>The Business Managers.</strong> The business managers shall act whenever the association has programs, parties, or undertakings with other associations.</li>
                                    <li><strong>The Advisers.</strong> The present school Administrative Officer, the Deputy Campus Director, and the Campus Director shall act as advisers of the association.</li>
                                </ol>
                                
                                </br>

                                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-center">ARTICLE VI - MEETING</h2>
                                <ol class="list-decimal ml-4">
                                    <li>The regular meeting of the association shall be held inside LSPU Library/Multipurpose hall at 4:00 p.m. every second Friday of the month. The members shall be notified by the secretary in a way that the members shall have ample time to attend. The holding of any meeting shall be referred to the University Campus Director to avoid conflict with his schedule of activities.</li>
                                    <li>The special meeting shall be called for official/all members as the case arises.</li>
                                    <li>All the above meetings shall need an attendant of 1/2 + 1 of all occasions and all members to attain a quorum.</li>
                                    <li>All members are enjoined to attend the meetings to participate in any discussions.</li>
                                </ol>
                                
                                </br>

                                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-center">ARTICLE VII - MUTUAL AIDS</h2>
                                <ol class="list-decimal ml-4">
                                    <li>There shall be a mutual aid amounting to P 5000.00 from the association for all active members of the association for nuptial and sickness.
                                        <ol class="list-decimal ml-4">
                                            <strong>Definitions:</strong>
                                                <ol class="list-decimal ml-4">
                                                    <strong>A. Sickness:</strong>
                                                        <ol class="list-decimal ml-4">
                                                            <li>A member must be hospitalized.</li>
                                                            <li>Normal delivery, caesarian, miscarriage cases are excluded.</li>
                                                        </ol>
                                                    </li>
                                                    <strong>B. Nuptials:</strong> Member shall avail it only once.
                                                </ol>
                                            </li>
                                        </ol>
                                    </li>
                                    
                                    <li>There shall be a financial aid of P 5000.00 from the association and a voluntary contribution from the members of the association for the immediate member of the family of each member of the association in case of death and sickness.</li>
                                        <ol class="list-decimal ml-4">
                                            <strong>Definitions:</strong>
                                                <ol class="list-decimal ml-4">
                                                    <strong>A. Immediate member:</strong>
                                                        <ol class="list-decimal ml-4">
                                                            <li>Married member – wife, husband and all legitimate children.</li>
                                                            <li>Unmarried member – father, mother, unmarried brothers and sisters living with  them below 19 years of age.</li>
                                                        </ol>
                                                </ol>
                                            </li>
                                        </ol>
                                    <li>Financial assistance for sickness can be availed only once in a year for each member.</li>
                                    <li>All financial assistance / mutual aids given to members shall be taken from the membership fee.</li>
                                </ol>
                                
                                </br>

                                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-center">ARTICLE VIII - FUNDS AND MEMBERSHIP FEE</h2>
                                <ol class="list-decimal ml-4">
                                    <li>There shall be a membership fee/monthly due for every member of the association, the amount of which is P50.00 which shall be deducted from the salary every 7th day of the month.</li>
                                    <li>Twenty percent (20%) of the ANNUAL NET TOTAL COLLECTION of the membership fee (total collection less disbursement for financial assistance) will be allotted to the retired members and death benefits of members.</li>
                                    <li>Any money of the association shall be deposited to the Land Bank of the Philippines with the President, Treasurer, and Auditor as signatories on money withdrawals.</li>
                                    <li>The income of the FPA Canteen shall be used to finance projects/programs of the association.</li>
                                    <li>An amount of 500 pesos per month will be given to the LSPU Trust Fund as space rental aside from payment of monthly electric bill.</li>
                                    <li>Resigned members of the association are entitled to refund the unexpended balance of his/her total contribution.</li>
                                </ol>
                                
                                </br>

                                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-center">ARTICLE IX - AMENDMENTS</h2>
                                <ol class="list-decimal ml-4">
                                    <li>Any amendments or revisions of this Constitution may be proposed by the Association with a vote of 3/4 + 1 of all members.</li>
                                    <li>Any amendments to or revisions of this Constitution shall be valid when ratified by a majority of the members.</li>
                                </ol>
                                
                                </br>
                                
                                <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-center">ARTICLE X - TRANSITORY PROVISIONS</h2>
                                <ol class="list-decimal ml-4">
                                    <li>The present set of officers shall act as interim officers of the association until the members of the regular officers shall have been elected or as provided in Sec. 4 and 6 Article IV.</li>
                                    <li>The interim officers shall have the same powers, functions, responsibilities, rights, and privileges as the regular officers thereof.</li>
                                    <li>All acts promulgated, issued, or done by the interim officers shall be part of the rules and regulations of the Association and shall remain valid, legal, and binding effective unless modified, revoked, or superseded by subsequent acts of the regular officers to be elected.</li>
                                </ol>
